- Returns SAME incidentId: d21e70ca-9d97-403b-930f-1f4504b10c2d
- ✅ PASS — dedup works, no duplicate incident created

### Part 3: No duplicate triage message for deduped POST
- Alerts SQS queue contains exactly 2 messages:
  - One for the first incident (d21e70ca)
  - One for the third incident (2234281d, after window expiry)
- No message for the second POST (which was deduped)
- ✅ PASS

### Part 4: Third POST after dedup window expiry creates a new incident
- Set existing incident's createdAt to 2 hours in the past (simulating window expiry)
- POST same payload → 202 Accepted
- Returns DIFFERENT incidentId: 2234281d-2f12-417f-8e32-457e97e9cb67
- DynamoDB query confirms 2 distinct incidents for same sourceAlertId=alert-001
- ✅ PASS

## Summary
All 4 boundary conditions of AC-015 pass:
1. First identical POST → new incident created
2. Second identical POST within dedup window → existing incident returned (dedup)
3. No duplicate triage SQS message for the deduped POST
4. Third identical POST after window expiry → new incident created

Working tree: clean (no tracked files changed)

## Verdict
qa=true implementation=true integration=true

# QA Journal - WI-AC-033 (VAPID web push subscription + push on incident change)

## Test Date
2026-07-09

## Work Item
WI-AC-033

## Environment
- OSS runtime with Postgres, Redis, running in Docker (core-causeflow-api-1)
- PORT mapped: 3099 (host) → 5171 (container)
- VAPID keys: configured (VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY + VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY)
- Auth: OSS login (JWT via /v1/auth/register + /v1/auth/login)
- Push subscription repo: PgPushSubscriptionRepository (Postgres-backed)

## Acceptance Check
AC-033: "Subscribe a browser to VAPID web push: POST /api/v1/notifications/subscribe with the endpoint + keys. On any incident severity change, the subscriber receives a push with the incident title and a deep link to /dashboard/incidents/:id. Revoking the subscription via DELETE removes the push record."

## Verification Results

### 1. POST /v1/notifications/subscribe — PASS
- Returns 200 `{"ok":true}` with valid endpoint + keys
- Returns 400 when endpoint is missing
- Returns 400 when keys.p256dh is missing
- Returns 400 when keys.auth is missing
- Returns 501 when push subscription repo is not configured (code path check)
- Returns 401 without valid auth token
- Repository `upsert` is called with correct data (validated via unit test)
- Real HTTP test against running server confirmed all above behaviors

### 2. Push notification fires on incident status change — PASS (partial)
- Event handler wired in bootstrap.ts for `incident.status_changed`
- Push is attempted to all tenant subscribers (confirmed via server logs)
- Deep link URL is correct: `/dashboard/incidents/{incidentId}`
- Tenant isolation holds: only the correct tenant's subscribers get push
- Unit tests validate push payload structure

### 3. Push notification contains incident title — FAIL
- The `incident.status_changed` event payload does NOT include the incident `title`
- All four emission sites only send `{ incidentId, from, to, actorUserId, actorEmail }`
- Handler falls back to "Incident updated" string
- AC-033 requires "the subscriber receives a push with the incident title"

### 4. DELETE /v1/notifications/subscribe — PASS
- Returns 200 `{"ok":true}` when endpoint exists
- Returns 200 `{"ok":true}` for non-existent endpoint (idempotent)
- Supports endpoint in request body or query parameter
- Returns 400 when no endpoint provided
- Returns 501 when push subscription repo is not configured
- Repository `delete` is called with correct endpoint

## Defects

### Defect 1: Push notification payload missing incident title
- Severity: medium
- Expected: Push contains the actual incident title (e.g. "CPU spike detected")
- Observed: Push says "Incident updated" (generic fallback)
- Root cause: All four `incident.status_changed` event emitters omit the `title` field
- Evidence: Code audit of all 4 emission sites + bootstrap.ts handler logic
- Fix: Add `title` to the event payload at all 4 emission sites, or fetch incident from repo in the push handler

### Defect 2: Push triggered on status change, not severity change
- Severity: low
- Expected: "On any incident severity change" per AC-033
- Observed: Triggered on `incident.status_changed` (status lifecycle events)
- Note: There is no separate "severity change" mechanism in the current architecture; severity is set at creation


---

# QA Journal - WI-AC-033 (VAPID web push) — Re-verification after defect fixes

## Test Date
2026-07-09

## Work Item
WI-AC-033

## Environment
- OSS runtime with Postgres, Redis, running in Docker (core-causeflow-api-1)
- PORT: 3099
- VAPID keys: configured (in container env)
- Auth: OSS JWT via POST /v1/auth/register + /v1/auth/login
- Push subscription repo: PgPushSubscriptionRepository (Postgres-backed)

## Previous QA Verdict (2026-07-09, commit 9a54877a)
qa=true implementation=false
Defects:
1. Push notification missing incident title (falls back to "Incident updated")
2. Push triggered on status change, not severity change (per AC-033)

## Fixes Applied (commits 69213f63 + 5fba77ca)
1. Added `title` field to `IncidentSeverityChangedEvent` payload interface
2. All 4 emission sites now include `title` in `severity_changed` events
3. New `incident.severity_changed` event type replaces `status_changed` for push trigger
4. Bootstrap handler subscribes to `severity_changed` with explicit comment that status transitions do not send pushes
5. WebPushAdapter uses dynamic import for better CJS/ESM interop
6. PushSubscriptionEntity added to ElectroDB entity registry
7. PgPushSubscriptionRepository handles upsert/list/delete/deleteAllByTenant
8. POST and DELETE /v1/notifications/subscribe routes with validation

## Verification Results

### 1. POST /v1/notifications/subscribe — PASS
- 200 with valid endpoint + keys
- 400 for missing endpoint, keys.p256dh, keys.auth
- 501 when push repo not configured
- 401 without auth token
- Subscription persisted in `causeflow.push_subscriptions` table
- Tenant-isolated storage

### 2. DELETE /v1/notifications/subscribe — PASS
- 200 on successful deletion
- 200 idempotent for non-existent endpoint
- Supports body and query param
- 400 when no endpoint provided
- Record removed from Postgres

### 3. Push on incident.severity_changed — PASS
- Server logs confirm push sending was attempted
- Push payload includes `title` from event (not fallback)
- Deep link: `/dashboard/incidents/{incidentId}` matches spec
- Fires on severity change, not on every status transition

### 4. Unit Tests — PASS
- 15 tests in ac033-push-subscription.test.ts all pass
- Type errors in test file fixed (body type annotations)

## Defects
None. Both previously reported defects have been resolved.

## Verdict
qa=true implementation=true
